---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: "help_output(& [\"audit\", \"all\", \"--help\"])"
---
Audit every repo in the GitHub org

Usage: hpds audit all [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --org <ORG>          GitHub organization to sweep [default: StanfordHPDS]
  -v, --verbose            Show more detail (underlying commands, tool names)
      --limit <N>          Audit at most this many repos when enumerating the org [default: 100]
  -q, --quiet              Suppress all output except errors
      --no-clone           Skip cloning: audit GitHub metadata only (runs just the watchers, contributors, and stale-remote-branches checks; the other checks need a working tree)
      --no-color           Disable colored output
      --config <PATH>      Use this config file instead of discovering hpds.toml
      --repos-from <FILE>  Audit the repos listed in FILE (one `owner/name` slug or local path per line, `#` comments allowed) instead of enumerating the org
      --output <PATH>      Write the markdown report to PATH [default: hpds-audit-report.md]
      --format <FORMAT>    Output format for the terminal summary [default: text] [possible values: text, json]
  -h, --help               Print help
